FT  23 SEP 93 / International Company News: Trade starts in Tribasa on NYSE
GRUPO TRIBASA, Mexico's second-largest construction company, started trading
on the New York Stock Exchange yesterday after making an initial public
offering of Dollars 263m in international markets, about a third of total
capital, writes Damian Fraser in Mexico City.
The offering was priced at Dollars 15.50 per American depositary receipt
(ADR). 21
The US took 50 per cent of the shares, Europe 30 per cent and Mexico 20 per
cent. The underwriter said the offering was over-subscribed in all markets.
